The reefs are rich in coral species and home to up to 1,000 species of fish.
But the world second-largest barrier reef the Mesoamerican Reef in the Caribbean is endangered runoff and pollution.
Warming waters from climate change commercial fishing development and ship groundings are jeopardizing them.
Caribbean coral species essential to the region reef ecosystems are at risk of extinction as a result of climate change.
Meanwhile a host of diseases plague coral many of them understood.
And as oceans warm algae that live in corals and on which they depend be killed.

